- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the efficiency and overhead reduction in mobile communication networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a hybrid scheme for managing interference in wireless communication systems. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper mentions high data rate demanding applications of mobile devices. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a novel approach for improving the sum rate in wireless communication systems.
